### Summary of Changes in Pull Request #145700

#### Bugs Fixed:
- Resolves issue with incorrect handling of null values in query parsing.
- Fixes race condition in document indexing process that could lead to data loss.
- Addresses memory leak in the aggregation framework affecting long-running queries.

#### Functional Changes:
- Added support for new query parameters in the search API to enhance flexibility.
- Improved error messages for invalid queries to aid in debugging.
- Enhanced the performance of document retrieval by optimizing the caching mechanism.

#### Refactoring:
- Refactored query parser code for better readability and maintainability.
- Removed deprecated methods and updated code to use the latest library versions.
- Extracted common logic into utility functions to reduce code duplication.

This PR aims to improve overall stability and performance of the Elasticsearch core features while addressing several long-standing bugs.